      <div class="two-column__one flow prose">
        <h3>Real World Location Research</h3>
        <p>When applicable I like to look at real world places as inspirations for my level designs on Google Maps. I had employed the method before but after listening to the talk <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cCsMz5tUXmc" rel="noopener">"Google Maps, not Grey Boxes: Digital Location Scouting for Untitled Goose Game" by Jake Strasser* at GDC 2021</a>, one of the makers of “Untitled Goose Game", I was all the more convinced that this is a fruitful approach and especially suitable for this prototype.</p> 

        <p>
          I knew there would be plenty of source material for American “Suburbia", the setting of the game, where I could not travel to but find it on Google Maps. Furthermore, there were some parallels between the Trash and Stash Prototype and "Untitled Goose Game" and if it was helpful for the team of “House House" it would probably be helpful for me as well.
        </p>
